label chapter_1_season_1_studying_narrations:
    $ dice_roll = renpy.random.randint(1, 4)

    if dice_roll == 1:
        "You lay out your books to study - back to Psych 101. The school may have changed, but parts of the curriculum sure haven't. The subject brings back bad memories, but the normality of it all is comforting, if nothing else."
    elif dice_roll == 2:
        "You begin to study for your World Politics class. The subject was never an easy one, but it's suddenly become a lot more complex, and your place in it has shifted dramatically of late. . ."
    elif dice_roll == 3:
        "'Mutant Physiology' was never a topic you had to think of before, but, as with most things in your life of late, you're having to reconsider it. And you thought high school biology was hard. . ."
    elif dice_roll == 4:
        "You (reluctantly) begin studying for Calculus. Your seething hatred for derivatives grows as you sincerely start to question why you picked training in the Danger Room over {i}this{/i}."

    return

label chapter_1_season_2_studying_narrations:
    $ dice_roll = renpy.random.randint(1, 4)

    if dice_roll == 1:
        "You settle down to study with a hot drink. It almost makes Calculus tolerable. Almost."
    elif dice_roll == 2:
        "You prepare to study for your upcoming Mutant Physiology test. Labeling the various types of wings mutants can have is difficult given the myriad forms that particular mutation can express itself, and you're fairly certain one of the wings in here belongs to a pelican."
    elif dice_roll == 3:
        "You sit down to work on your Combat & Strategic Planning paper. This time, you have to watch three action movies and explain the mistakes made in each one. Sometimes, being at this school can be pretty damn awesome."
    elif dice_roll == 4:
        "You decide to take things easy for a change. The snow is falling outside, your room is warm and you have a flask of hot chocolate sitting beside you, so you spend some time rereading your notes and writing up some topics to study when you get the chance."

    return

label chapter_1_season_3_studying_narrations:
    $ dice_roll = renpy.random.randint(1, 4)

    if dice_roll == 1:
        "You sit down to study for your class on Mutant Culture. You're not entirely sure about Lila Cheney's music, but she's definitely making the retro thing work for her!"
    elif dice_roll == 2:        
        "You study for this week's Psychic Defense class. The professor implanted the answers to next week's test directly into the minds of everyone attending the class, now you have to work out how to access them. Nothing is ever simple around here. . ."
    elif dice_roll == 3:
        "You study for your Mutant Physiology class, learning about the similarities and differences shared by shapeshifting abilities and healing factors. You make a note to meet up with [Laura.name] and ask her a few questions later."
    elif dice_roll == 4:
        "You decide to study outside and get roped into being the ref for a game of basketball. You don't actually have to do anything though, you're just there to make sure no one uses their powers to cheat. You don't have that much control of your powers yet, but they don't know that, so you actually manage to get some studying done."

    return

label chapter_1_season_4_studying_narrations:
    $ dice_roll = renpy.random.randint(1, 4)

    if dice_roll == 1:
        "One last burst of effort to get things wrapped up. The end of the year is so close, you can almost taste it!"
    elif dice_roll == 2:        
        "You're preparing for your Mutant Physiology final, working on an essay about the definition of 'Omega' level mutants and, at this point, you're willing to bet everything you own that whoever created these terms was just making this shit up as they went along."
    elif dice_roll == 3:       
        "Staring down the barrel of your Calculus final, you decide that, next term, you'll go with something less harmful to your mental health. . . But it's all for a good cause. And as soon as you can remember what that cause is, you'll probably start to feel a bit better."
    elif dice_roll == 4:
        "Getting ready for your Psych final and you're surprised at how far you've come. The changes have been thick and fast this year, but you've met them astonishingly well. Just this final hurdle and you're free and clear for the year!"

    return